/org_eclipse_platform/org_eclipse_osgi/ConfigAdminListenerInnerLoggerContextConfigurationTest.java`\n- Added `org.osgi.service.cm` test dependency so the Equinox framework can expose Configuration Admin types:\n  - `tests/src/org.eclipse.platform/org.eclipse.osgi/3.18.300/build.gradle`\n- Made the existing placeholder top-level test class public to satisfy the repository rule:\n  - `tests/src/org.eclipse.platform/org.eclipse.osgi/3.18.300/src/test/java/org_eclipse_platform/org_eclipse_osgi/Org_eclipse_osgiTest.java`\n\nThe new test starts an embedded Equinox framework, registers a mock `ConfigurationAdmin`, exercises initial configuration loading, obtains the registered `SynchronousConfigurationListener`, and sends update/delete `ConfigurationEvent`s. This should drive the constructor proxy/class/method lookup sites plus the `register`, `getReference`, `getEventPid`, `getType`, and `findConfiguration` reflective invocation paths for the active inner class.\n\nI did not compile or run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c5cf2bd2ea7cb7d0169fa42239274819f8c275ce731faaf3b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1564, "output": 772, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36128, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778008600413, "responseId": "resp_0c5cf2bd2ea7cb7d0169fa4219075c819f974723fb8e8ee24e"}, "toolResults": []}
